Muscle strain is one of the most common injuries in tennis.[81] When an isolated large-energy appears during the muscle contraction and at the same time body weight apply huge amount of pressure to the lengthened muscle, muscle strain can occur.[82] Inflammation and bleeding are triggered when muscle strain occurs, which can result in redness, pain and swelling.[82] Overuse is also common in tennis players of all levels. Muscle, cartilage, nerves, bursae, ligaments and tendons may be damaged from overuse. The repetitive use of a particular muscle without time for repair and recovery is the most common cause of injury.[82]
